    "body": "### Problem\n\n`q:` does not clear the `:` from the pending character buffer. A operation resulting in operator pending (like `\"`) results in `:\"` showed as pending while only `\"` is actually pending\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n1. Press `q`, `:`, `\"` which results in `:q` in the preview while only `\"` is actually pending (register selection)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should reset the buffer and only show the actually pending characters\ni.e. for `q`, `:`, `\"` it should be just `\"`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, but still a bug (9.1.2024)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.05\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nsligthly outdated nixpkgs version",
